From b6bee15c1ce6e42e5a395cb73cd8908992414dd2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Basti <89860334+Xerolux@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 13:56:14 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] Add Debian Trixie / Python 3.13+ support with platform
 detection

Major changes:
- New platform_detect.sh: detects RPi/x86/VM, architecture, Debian version
- Virtual environment at /opt/openwb-venv (avoids PEP 668 conflicts)
- install_packages.sh: platform-aware package installation (no python3-pip,
  no python3-urllib3, conditional GUI/RPi packages, evdev only when available)
- atreboot.sh: uses venv pip, platform-aware boot config (RPi only),
  display detection (skips tvservice on non-RPi/VM)
- openwb-install.sh: creates venv, auto-detects PHP version for upload limit
- Service files: use /opt/openwb-venv/bin/python3 for all ExecStart
- requirements.txt: removed asyncio shim, evdev commented (platform-specific)
- Python fixes: datetime.utcnow() -> datetime.now(timezone.utc) (3 files)
- Python fixes: #!/usr/bin/python -> #!/usr/bin/env python3 (2 files)
- create_debug.py: guard vcgencmd calls for non-RPi systems
- CI: test against Python 3.10, 3.12, 3.13 matrix
- README: update supported OS versions (Bookworm/Trixie)
